# Assembly Definition Boundaries

- Keep `Editor` code inside editor-only assemblies; do not leak `UnityEditor` or editor tooling dependencies into runtime assemblies.
- `Domain` assemblies must not reference `UnityEngine`, `UnityEditor`, Photon Fusion, scene objects, or infrastructure implementations.
- `Application` runtime logic may depend on `Domain` and shared contracts; do not add `Presentation` or `Editor` references.
- Photon Fusion assembly references must stay out of `Domain` and pure `Application`; place Fusion-dependent code in networking adapters under `Presentation`, `Infrastructure`, or `Bootstrap`.
- `ScriptableObject` config authoring types under `Application` may reference UnityEngine, but this exception must not carry scene objects, `MonoBehaviour`, IO, or presentation dependencies.
- Test assemblies should reference only the layer under test, required test frameworks, and explicit runtime contracts.
- If a new feature pushes `asmdef` dependency direction outside `Domain <- Application <- Presentation`, fix the architecture before adding the reference.
- If there is no `asmdef`, question whether a new assembly is actually needed before adding one.

## Example

```csharp
// BAD: Domain assembly takes a Unity dependency
using UnityEngine;

// GOOD: Domain stays pure; Unity needs are handled in adapter/editor assemblies
public sealed class OrderRule { }
```
